Reservation is not poverty relief. It’s caste justice.

When leaders say “economic status” should replace caste, they show how little they understand the lived reality of Dalits. A Dalit can be educated, employed, even wealthy, and still face untouchability, discrimination, and exclusion. Money doesn’t erase caste.

That’s why reservation exists. And yet, both BJP and INDI Alliance politicians refuse to see this truth.

Dalits owe allegiance to no party. Because no party has truly stood by them.

Let's understand your chances of getting a decent-income job that matches inflation and allows you to save money in Urban India (I mean top 10 cities).

This is the maths behind reservation, we need to increase representation in the proportion of their probability to reach high income jobs.

Copy pasting.

In Government Job, (35K Jobs per year)
5K Group A 75% employees from Urban India
30K Group B 65% employees from Urban India

In Corporate/Private Job (1.65L Jobs per year)
10LPA+ 90% employees from Urban India.

It means there are hardly 15% chance to get a decent job if you don't belong to Urban India

In Urban India, top 20 crore population, 50% belongs to upper caste Hindu and almost 80% in middle class.

Female Labour Participation is 20% in India which means upper caste hindu female had 16% chance and other female had 4%.

For upper caste Hindu male of Urban India's social mobility we need almost 5 times more decent job from Chinese perspective and almost 10 times more decent job from US European perspective.
